(* Beginning of Notebook Content *)
Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["A Mathematica Primer", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"e4e45870-86a1-8442-9af8-f67a3cbe5a0e"],

Cell["\<\
This is a bare-bones Mathematica primer (courtesy of Prof. Richard Sorbello). \
Some basic commands for calculations and plots are given.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785661592929955`*^9, 
  3.9785661704130707`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0c1f386f-8409-c04b-8a16-\
2338946004db"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A large set of useful commands and examples may be found at ",
 ButtonBox["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/"]
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a234276a-cc7e-3842-a554-fa23e0ba3292"],

Cell["\<\
(* Mathematica is the desktop application; the programming language is the \
Wolfram Language. You can run the same notebooks in Wolfram Desktop or \
Wolfram Cloud (browser). The Documentation Center pages include runnable \
examples and exact argument patterns. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"b453968a-2623-dc4b-b8e8-2163d8333365"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Basic steps for a Mathematica calculation", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ba175d8c-6165-464c-ba2c-9a17a5e75874"],

Cell["1. Start up Mathematica. An \"Untitled-1\" window will appear.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"551c7196-987a-6f47-92af-2f86350719d3"],

Cell["\<\
(* In Wolfram Cloud, you'll instead see a new cloud notebook in your browser. \
Both environments share the same language and evaluation model. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"40dcbaf1-64a3-0c40-95fe-a47ea00df294"],

Cell["\<\
2. You will automatically be in the \"input\" command mode. Type a \
Mathematica command in the window.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8b60122e-3fe0-674b-8f9a-238f787adb88"],

Cell["\<\
Some examples are given in the session printed out below. Be very careful \
with syntax.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1c86b087-d109-e242-a67e-b04aec84f352"],

Cell["\<\
Pay special attention, for example, whether you should type \")\" or \"]\" or \
\"}\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1f633f23-0605-bc46-a1d4-d4c62393a7c8"],

Cell["\<\
As an illustration, suppose that you have specified a value for the quantity \
x and you want to evaluate the sine of x.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"71b7194c-a055-4345-8ea7-c242872be917"],

Cell["\<\
This must be written as Sin[x] and not sin[x] or sin(x) or Sin(x).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fb3692fb-75be-8b4f-b817-25b23f3651e2"],

Cell["\<\
Note that all built-in Mathematica function commands begin with an upper case \
letter, and the argument must be enclosed by square brackets.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1e51d21-ab5d-7141-969f-b80f1a29e0da"],

Cell["\<\
To find the correct syntax for various commands and functions, you can use \
the Help menu at the top of the screen when you are in the Mathematica \
program.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"99aca62e-4d72-6046-936b-94d946bc1265"],

Cell["\<\
(* Use inline documentation: type a function name and press Shift+Ctrl+K \
(Windows/Linux) or Cmd+Shift+K (macOS) to open its guide; autocompletion and \
function templates (tabbing through slots) reduce syntax errors. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"3c5bf60b-ca97-4040-8910-f6009d45bba8"],

Cell["\<\
3. After typing in your Mathematica command, press \"shift-return\", which \
means pressing the \"shift\" and \"return\" keys simultaneously.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"102dd3de-9c67-8540-9b2b-b3de2b3d8788"],

Cell["\<\
(For full-size keyboards, just pressing the \"enter\" key on the numeric \
keypad also works.) After the output is displayed, you may type another input \
command, press \"shift-return\" again, and continue the session in this way.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"50ffbb69-1582-fc44-9814-12b7c8d41349"],

Cell["\<\
If, instead of working with one command at a time, you wish to set up a \
series of commands, you can type them sequentially, pressing \"return\" after \
each one.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ce16ebdf-89ef-1b40-be80-7aacba4bb632"],

Cell["\<\
Mathematica will not evaluate these commands until you press \"shift-return\" \
or \"enter\", at which time the entire block of commands will be sequentially \
evaluated.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"da6437e8-e873-e242-a4f1-bab43575130e"],

Cell["\<\
(If you wish to suppress the print out of the result of any one of these \
commands in your block of commands, put a semicolon at the end of that \
command.)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d2c1a377-3011-be42-a0de-fe84e9a89918"],

Cell["\<\
(* Use Alt+Enter to insert a new line without evaluating (platform-dependent; \
check menu). Evaluation Abort Evaluation stops a runaway computation; \
Evaluation Quit Kernel fully resets the session. Semicolons; remain the \
standard way to suppress printed output. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"4cba2900-80cf-ab45-83ac-6078c681088f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Cautionary Advice:", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d614cdee-a0a7-304a-9b09-1b36a86b7e39"],

Cell["\<\
1. You may always use the explicit asterisk symbol for multiplication.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7da137f2-2be2-ef47-9d0d-2de96addd5c2"],

Cell["\<\
However, for aesthetic purposes, you can just leave a blank space (or more \
than one blank space) between symbols to be multiplied.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8988d2c8-181f-8942-8804-7ee43d1d5243"],

Cell["\<\
If you do this, be very careful. For example, the product \"a\" times \"x\" \
can be written as \"ax\" or as \"a x\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c0d1e96f-7a2f-9546-af1b-6d39b7747536"],

Cell["\<\
If you type \"ax\" you are referring to a single variable whose name consists \
of the two letters \"a\" and \"x\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"29ef50a8-e16d-b744-b24b-ea28338c4ddd"],

Cell["\<\
In the special case of a number pre-multiplying a variable, you are not \
required to write the product using an asterisk or a space or a set of \
enclosing round-parentheses.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"74cc1e87-37e7-d345-a964-a94df354feb6"],

Cell["\<\
For example, you can type \"2x\" without a space between the \"2\" and \"x\" \
and this will be understood by Mathematica to be 2 times x, just as if you \
wrote \"2x\" or \"2 x\" or 2(x).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c1447999-188a-fb45-ba14-06981de2bb08"],

Cell["\<\
Although the multiplication symbol \"*\" may tend to clutter long \
expressions, it's a good idea to use it if you have not yet become proficient \
in Mathematica.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fb8e8419-c805-d54d-8bab-ec11e678a7a5"],

Cell["\<\
(* Implicit multiplication (e.g., 2x, a x) is convenient but easy to misuse \
when variables have multi-letter names; prefer explicit * until comfortable. \
For typeset input, palettes avoid ambiguity. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"b7dcbed0-6325-0f49-91fc-ab346b6f3bdc"],

Cell["\<\
2. A common error that users of Mathematica run into occurs when they attempt \
to plot an expression that is not real or has no numerical value because it \
was either not defined properly or the quantities within the expression do \
not have specific numerical values.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"80282afd-5dd4-544d-b79e-1b8c5f0d3dee"],

Cell["\<\
As an example, suppose that you try to plot an expression that you have \
called f that depends on the variable x, but the expression for f contains \
another quantity a that has not been given a numerical value.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4fbec7af-70f4-9b47-8a56-6226262236fc"],

Cell["\<\
For example, f = Sin[x] + a*Cos[x], with no value for a specified.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"32ab8fcd-96f8-db4d-a9c4-d5f2eaada42c"],

Cell["\<\
Now suppose that you type the plot command Plot[f, {x, 0, 10}] to plot f \
between x=0 and x=10. Mathematica will give you a series of error messages: \
\"f is not a machine-size real number at x= ...\" and display an empty plot.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fc59f1bb-23f5-a34a-b9c1-7aa5d06d4f9c"],

Cell["\<\
To fix this, define your expression correctly, i.e., specify a value for a \
before you type the plot command.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1f05fd99-e3e8-d649-b206-71426fce17ca"],

Cell["\<\
(* When plotting, ensure the function is numeric for numeric x. If you define \
a function, write F[x_?NumericQ] := Sin[x] + a Cos [x] /. a->1 or supply \
parameters explicitly in the plot. Plot/NIntegrate evaluate numerically; \
non-numeric subexpressions cause these warnings. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"8b54f73f-8e36-1c4c-b01a-e0d4ed846f6f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Cells", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"809a2135-a07b-d64d-91ee-917d63a60864"],

Cell["\<\
Your output will appear in a \"cell\" just below your input line.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"17a220f7-f9b2-004d-82aa-a5cf3c70b3d5"],

Cell["\<\
The \"cells\" are denoted by the blue brackets on the right of the screen.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bdbd12f5-6752-a740-b2c9-f36812cde37f"],

Cell["\<\
The output cell will be grouped with your input command cell inside an outer \
cell bracket signifying the entire cell group.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6a759897-b3ad-aa48-a81b-be7383d423c8"],

Cell["\<\
You can select any cell by clicking on the cell bracket with the mouse.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"894a18d4-ac13-5546-aa63-9a0d32ecd34a"],

Cell["\<\
To correct a previous calculation: Type your corrections in the command, \
click on the cell bracket, and press \"shift-return\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b4820010-c9ce-6246-a84e-044c93b607cc"],

Cell["\<\
The new output will then over-write the previous output. (Alternatively, \
instead of selecting the cell bracket, you can just click on any point in the \
cell containing the command lines.) You can delete any cell or cell group by \
selecting the cell or cell group and using the delete key.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cd9bdda6-bc48-4f49-ab3c-5dcf77362bb4"],

Cell["\<\
To close or open-up a group of cells: Double-click on the cell bracket.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fadd97fb-8762-6f47-b133-62eca6ad2f35"],

Cell["\<\
(A darkened lower corner of a bracket indicates a closed cell group.) To \
merge cells, select them (drag mouse over the brackets of the desired cells) \
and use menu item \"Cell/Merge Cells\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fb0cb78b-c288-2649-8be8-95872d282aa2"],

Cell["Grouping controls to manage structure.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8f1b9739-6b36-534f-a775-0d2afdbf0756"],

Cell["\<\
(* Modern notebooks show slim gray group brackets; use Cell manage structure. \
For presentations, apply Format Style (Section/Subsection/Text/Input) so \
notebooks produce a usable outline. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"ef4a803d-6328-d749-ae87-241e3a0fdf72"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Palettes", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"e8043b8d-109e-f64d-806c-8c419a36eb87"],

Cell["\<\
As an alternative to typing command-lines, use palettes by choosing the menu \
item Palettes at the top of the screen in recent versions of Mathematica or \
use the menu item File/Palettes in earlier versions.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e2bdce5b-f0bd-5147-bd96-3723171cbe4e"],

Cell["\<\
To create your command, use the \"Basic Math Input\" palette (or \"Basic \
Input\" palette in earlier versions), and type the desired variables or \
numbers in the template slots, then press \"shift-return\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"98818fab-4c48-5d43-bddd-2fc1f4c854d1"],

Cell["\<\
You can navigate sequentially through template slots by pressing \"tab\" key, \
or else use the mouse.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3b978975-43be-5747-a3c2-ec2a95f56d3e"],

Cell["\<\
Note that with the Basic Math Input palette, you can enter Greek letters, and \
for example, enter \"p\" instead of having to type \"Pi\" for 3.14159...\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"62f40cc6-9799-8146-ad9c-a809aee9de28"],

Cell["\<\
(* Also try Basic Math Assistant and Classroom Assistant palettes (with \
ready-made templates for integrals, sums, matrices). Greek letters can be \
inserted via palettes or by Esc-shortcuts (below); full symbolic names like \
\[Gamma] also work. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"45fa10bc-96a1-5b43-b86f-858f849137e0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Input Mode and Text Mode", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"df80b874-52e0-0847-903c-d7ff24ba57fc"],

Cell["\<\
When you type in your window you will normally be in the input mode in which \
case what you type will be interpreted as Mathematica commands.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"539f0e92-1775-ac46-8694-99b8e7b1219b"],

Cell["\<\
The typed characters appear boldface in this mode. However, you might want to \
add blocks of text to annotate your work or to create a notebook, and this \
requires you to start a cell in Text Mode.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8f2661c8-b254-6745-aa6f-720bf4abb771"],

Cell["\<\
To do this position your cursor (click) outside and below your previous cell \
group, and choose Format/Style/Text, or use a keyboard shortcut.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d874f57d-7f70-994c-95ac-61a85bf4b711"],

Cell["\<\
(* Use Section/Subsection/Text styles to scaffold explanations, then keep \
code in Input cells. For reproducibility, mark shared definitions as \
Initialization Cells (Cell Properties) and run them via Evaluation Evaluate \
Initialization Cells. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"6e9128a3-1654-6640-b6df-92ec452fdcff"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Keyboard Shortcuts for Menu Items", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b4e56578-e6d5-ef49-b40b-273cedfed006"],

Cell["\<\
To find the appropriate keyboard shortcut for a specific menu item, use the \
menu for the given item and note the keyboard symbol listed next to that item.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"10fd4e12-a611-fb44-84b7-81c321d8dc69"],

Cell["\<\
Subsequently, you can use this keyboard shortcut instead of using the menu.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fbb6492b-42fc-7c43-8b55-89082f732888"],

Cell["\<\
For example, here are some keyboard shortcuts for Mathematica on a Macintosh \
computer (Microsoft Windows and other operating systems have their own set of \
keyboard shortcuts, which you can find by going to the menu item as just \
described.):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dff1b82b-7c75-b643-8f4a-760ebe7c661b"],

Cell["- Copy: \"Cmd-C\"; Paste: \"Cmd-V\"; Cut: \"Cmd-X\"", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b48486d4-4885-e84f-9be4-846506123943"],

Cell["- Undo: \"Cmd-Z\"; Select All: \"Cmd-A\"; Save: \"Cmd-S\"", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9a772d81-e265-444d-b225-fa40067b8a56"],

Cell["\<\
- Abort Calculation: \"Cmd-.\" (or \"Evaluation/Abort Evaluation\" or \
\"Kernel/Abort Evaluation\" on the menu bar)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fe32c11f-96bb-564a-a570-f9f7e89e903c"],

Cell["\<\
- Text-mode style: \"Cmd-7\" (or \"Format/Style/Text\" on the menu bar)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7a7f803f-22f9-3549-ab96-82e2e79c6a7e"],

Cell["\<\
- Return to Input-mode style: \"Cmd-9\" (or \"Format/Style/Input\" on the \
menu bar)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1fca3641-f45b-9649-9c6c-1ba06d73e540"],

Cell["\<\
- Bold text (in textmode): \"Cmd-B\". Toggle (press \"Cmd-B\" again) to turn \
bold text off.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d3eec470-80d7-854b-984d-e2f1d4ec0051"],

Cell["\<\
- Italic text (in textmode): \"Cmd-I\". Toggle (press \"Cmd-I\" again) to \
turn italic text off.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d4301143-0c8a-c04b-907e-c48e4e077dd1"],

Cell["\<\
Here \"Cmd\" is the \"Command\" key, also known as the \"Apple\" or \
\"Flower\" key, and appears to the immediate left of the space-bar on a \
Macintosh keyboard.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fc329247-aad7-eb4c-8648-d972ab65a0b3"],

Cell["\<\
\"Cmd-C\", for example, means hold down the \"Command\" key while pressing \
the \"C\" key on the keyboard.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a438329b-c09d-604f-a73b-cd2dd5821282"],

Cell["\<\
(The use of upper case letters in denoting a keystroke such as Cmd-C, etc., \
does not signify typing an upper-case C, etc.)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4e2abc7d-aab5-fe45-b0b1-15974d9af268"],

Cell["\<\
(* On Windows/Linux, platform equivalents appear alongside menu items (e.g., \
Ctrl+C, Ctrl+V). Abort Evaluation is often Alt+. on Windows; always check the \
Evaluation menu for your OS. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"c6567b14-f3b4-d646-9055-6ece01a6f090"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Keyboard Shortcuts for Greek letters", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b72332ed-6034-d443-9e43-0f8638ea0d51"],

Cell["\<\
It is convenient to use keyboard shortcuts for writing Greek letters.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"29bc34f8-0e74-2a40-ba2d-feaccd1d9f7e"],

Cell["\<\
The shortcut for a Greek letter is to sequentially press the escape key, the \
roman letter equivalent, and the escape key.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"23a09430-9f30-0e4a-9c92-21dad10b2cf2"],

Cell["\<\
For example, to type the lower-case Greek letter gamma, press esc, g, esc, \
where esc is the abbreviation for the escape key.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"20ac446d-a1b7-b24c-9d01-72361a3b2c9c"],

Cell["For capital gamma press esc, G, esc.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0ed11c35-787e-6142-8095-71e4cfdab80b"],

Cell["\<\
(* You can also type the long-form names \[Gamma], \[Alpha], etc., or use the \
palette buttons. Autocompletion proposes symbols once you start typing \\[. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"15b4e556-f832-9545-857b-48ac3b1c1666"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Examples of Calculations and Plots:", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"803140e3-66ab-4740-bfa0-1320bbf69817"],

Cell["\<\
In the Mathematica session below, note that Mathematica displays the input \
command-lines in boldface font, sequentially numbers them, and numbers the \
corresponding output-lines.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"502dd27c-4ee8-3d48-a026-79800a9009c7"],

Cell["\<\
(The explanatory text between some commands was created by going to \
Format/Style/Text to enter the text mode.)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"36d82aff-3e1e-3a45-a615-d3a502f5df0d"],

Cell["\<\
Pi and E are the appropriate Mathematica keyboard inputs for 3.14159... and \
2.71828..., respectively; the Basic Input palette symbols and Mathematica's \
output symbols for these quantities are p and e, respectively.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f8ae9ac2-3c45-9146-9722-11608c676fb0"],

Cell["\<\
N[expr] evaluates an expression expr numerically; N[expr, 40] evaluates expr \
to 40 digit precision (unless the numbers in expr are decimal or machine \
precision).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"29020a85-6a13-ed48-8062-c71ea71ec58e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The construction ",
 StyleBox["expr /. x->a", "Code"],
 " means return the value of expr for the case that x = a but do not change \
expr as a result of this evaluation."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2d6d17fe-53ba-cb4f-8f03-b3fbea990b9f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Integrate[f, {x, x1, x2}]", "Code"],
 " means analytically integrate f from x=x1 to x=x2; ",
 StyleBox["NIntegrate [f, {x, x1, x2}]", "Code"],
 " means numerically integrate f from x=x1 to x=x2. (The indefinite integral, \
or anti-derivative, is given by Integrate[f, x], but is not used in this \
session.)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"65d52bff-b9f5-4046-bd0a-a08323b22879"],

Cell["\<\
(* Use N[expr, n] with high precision inputs to propagate precision; \
SetPrecision/Rationalize make inputs exact when needed. For assumptions, wrap \
computations in Assuming [...] for cleaner symbolic results. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"a1e30484-81e8-1847-893c-2c49161fb265"],

Cell["\<\
The correct syntax for creating simple plots is illustrated by the example \
Plot[f, {x, 0, 3}] in input line 5.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cf13305b-5ca6-bb4a-87ba-9274d8ee535a"],

Cell["\<\
Note that in the example, Plot[f, {x, 0, 5}] entered in input line 6, \
Mathematica has decided on its own to display more detail of the oscillations \
of f for large values of x, and in doing so, was unable to fully display the \
peaks occurring in the range 1 > x > 0.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a5681205-eb37-e645-85bb-2be4913f8aba"],

Cell["\<\
To get Mathematica to give us the entire plot of f vs. x for 5 >= x >= 0, we \
use the command Plot[f, {x, 0, 5}, PlotRange -> All] in input line 7, where \
PlotRange -> All is the option that overrides Mathematica's occasional \
attempt to display features that it thinks we would like to see and instead \
tells Mathematica to show us everything.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"02ad7e5d-1307-0343-9f46-28d4932b5507"],

Cell["\<\
(Be sure to use the correct syntax, with \"PlotRange\" as a single word \
containing an upper case R.)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aa4016f3-3054-484f-8f76-566209475834"],

Cell["\<\
(* Add clarity with PlotLegends -> Automatic, AxesLabel -> {\"x\", \"y\"}, \
and themes such as Plot Theme -> \"Scientific\". When plotting lists of \
points, ListLinePlot is a convenient alternative to ListPlot[..., Joined -> \
True]. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"6a503d43-1461-b340-92cc-7e663da8296d"],

Cell[BoxData["Pi"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"17bdbdd7-0601-5641-aec5-15cc38eaf5b0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"N", "[", "Pi", "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0906f006-f84a-9b4e-a5d0-4c85c3c33ac2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"N", "[", "Pi", ",", "40", "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"18ec767d-8b18-4042-bff1-d6e17e3886e6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"f", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "x"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
     RowBox[{"10", " ", "x"}], "]"}], " ", 
    SuperscriptBox["E", 
     RowBox[{"-", "x"}]]}]}], ";"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"9c2071ce-d479-\
6b40-8f98-ac9256b41e81"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"f", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "3"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID\
->"6b14e136-dae5-ed42-8cf3-40c0c3282004"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"f", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "5"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID\
->"4d6d9f2b-4270-1f4f-ba93-c81e1df758de"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"f", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "5"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"7e1f3fc5-a92b-d54a-926d-4a967b974ece"],

Cell["Note: It is often desirable to label the plot axes.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bcc0869f-35c6-4b46-8999-9f9bfc5479bd"],

Cell["\<\
The option AxesLabel -> {\"xtext\", \"ytext\"} puts the text-string xtext on \
the x-axis and the text string ytext on the y-axis.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"596c1418-3a40-f445-940f-04dad1460ebc"],

Cell["\<\
For example, to place the symbol x on the x-axis and the symbol f on the \
y-axis, change the previous Plot command to:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e0aa2c5a-4a8b-a449-ae6b-c70c3d49e4e3"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"f", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "5"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"AxesLabel", "->", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<x\>\"", ",", "\"\<f\>\""}], "}"}]}]}], "]"}]], "Input",Expre\
ssionUUID->"8f9062d4-b2f4-a34d-ab3d-93abbed42146"],

Cell["\<\
To add the plot-label myplot, add the option PlotLabel -> \"myplot\", as for \
example:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ef73fa78-6e4f-9949-9133-82f9129d70f5"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"f", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "5"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"AxesLabel", "->", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<x\>\"", ",", "\"\<f\>\""}], "}"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotLabel", "->", "\"\<f = exp(-x) sin 10x\>\""}]}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"923214e3-2c74-e849-893b-080fd957c538"],

Cell["\<\
(* Prefer named colors (e.g., Red, Blue) or style themes over raw RGBColor \
[...] when teaching. Frame -> True and Frame Label often look cleaner in \
printed notes. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"d57c02b5-b5df-5149-a852-e9022ab9a9ec"],

Cell["\<\
In the next command, we integrate f from x=0 to x=b, and define the result to \
be z.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b78330fd-2e5e-b149-892e-f6b2012a3c1f"],

Cell["\<\
In input line 9, the quantity y is set equal to the value of z for b=1. The \
result for y is exact because the value of b has been taken to be exactly 1 \
and therefore all numbers in the output are also exact.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6bb3e599-e398-9d45-9f17-33a236bae1aa"],

Cell["To get a numerical value for y we use N[y].", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3b5dc2f6-3196-e844-9f28-5874cba5cdac"],

Cell["\<\
The result checks out to be the same as the numerical integration of f using \
the Nintegrate command, as it must.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4d63fbcf-42c6-114b-a5b4-f33ba741345c"],

Cell["\<\
(* For numeric integration stability, set Method and Working Precision as \
needed; use Assuming [b > 0, ...] to guide symbolic integration. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"9fafba23-dc05-8943-a0c3-23944bedf81f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"z", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Integrate", "[", 
   RowBox[{"f", ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "b"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionU\
UID->"3aaccdff-7eef-fb42-a678-e2750d9e7ec6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"y", "=", 
  RowBox[{"z", "/.", 
   RowBox[{"b", "->", "1"}]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"28ac5146-4bda-ad4e-\
9776-399c73253576"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"N", "[", "y", "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"2ed4d001-fc9c-d041-ac91-ee4bc409fc1a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"NIntegrate", "[", 
  RowBox[{"f", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID\
->"5248dea0-085a-fc48-84a2-cf122787b499"],

Cell["\<\
Example using Palettes: Click on definite integral template in the Basic Math \
Input (or Basic Input) palette, fill in slots sequentially, and press \
\"shift-return\".\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"22c2bc68-c242-1345-966d-cc657768c7e3"],

Cell["\<\
To evaluate the definite integral with b=1, you can use the % symbol \
(previous output) and attach the substitution rule /.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ec67da7c-e94d-0544-ad9d-4cbbb445f2b0"],

Cell["\<\
b->1, or copy/paste and replace b with 1. Results are equivalent (grouped \
slightly differently):\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aae62c2e-26b7-664f-a582-f28f9c39533e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"%", "/.", 
  RowBox[{"b", "->", "1"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a1878a27-5d83-fd4a-b8c5-a6ad0a79afb7"],

Cell["\<\
(* Palette-generated typeset input is handy for beginners; advanced users \
often prefer plain-text function forms (Integrate [ ]) for version control \
and readability. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"2b34660d-0ae8-9646-bf4d-df3cf9945b2a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Functions, tables, and their plots", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"75ac3c7c-2df8-fc4a-a6c1-2df32a9617ae"],

Cell["\<\
Instead of defining an expression such as f = Sin[10 x] E^(-x), it is often \
convenient to define the corresponding explicit function of x, and refer to \
the function as F[x].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2143db69-6c21-d04a-a1ac-bd16c2c31e70"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The syntax for defining this function is ",
 StyleBox["F[x_]:=Sin[10 x]E^(-x)", "Code"],
 ". (Note the := symbol, and the underscore after the variable on the \
left-hand side.)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f79439bf-8ffa-6f48-acdd-7b995cba2dfb"],

Cell["\<\
This construction makes the user-defined function F[x] act exactly as a \
Mathematica built-in function such as Sin[x] in that you can call F[x] \
repeatedly with different numerical or symbolic values of x, and F[x] is \
evaluated afresh each time.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"84f38f2d-c0de-e346-8b28-cedc102a568e"],

Cell["\<\
In the following commands, the function F[x] is defined and plotted, and a \
list named mylist is created using Table[...].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6cb7cbb3-c618-0f44-b164-862347c85c6c"],

Cell["\<\
The iterator {x, 0, 3, 0.1} means that x values are chosen from 0 to 3 in \
intervals of 0.1.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9f02a0b3-ffba-5042-908d-a0e37f085e6b"],

Cell["\<\
The resulting list consists of paired numbers. This list is displayed in a \
user-friendly tabular form with //TableForm.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6de61e07-e5e2-b146-8b2e-3e2a6657de6f"],

Cell["\<\
A plot of the pairs is made using ListPlot. The option Joined -> True \
connects the data points with straight segments.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fa1d297e-8f3b-a64c-8085-9aa5ebc41f32"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"F", "[", "x_", "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
    RowBox[{"10", " ", "x"}], "]"}], 
   SuperscriptBox["E", 
    RowBox[{"-", "x"}]]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"cb60e695-da16-044e-\
a5aa-f19a1e850faa"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"F", "[", "x", "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "3"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID\
->"d5483c39-6098-ed49-81a2-f8cd1b82c904"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"mylist", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", 
      RowBox[{"F", "[", "x", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "3", ",", "0.1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",\
ExpressionUUID->"17361799-de9d-d34c-b05b-9d5c21630bf3"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", 
      RowBox[{"F", "[", "x", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "3", ",", "0.1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "//", 
  "TableForm"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"f9095c0d-f6d0-c14e-8782-\
2484d451c3e8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", "mylist", "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7fdb8340-d8df-674e-adf3-083b443d5aa8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"mylist", ",", 
   RowBox[{"Joined", "->", "True"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"b3d2b295-45bb-4d41-9a71-1cd5c3730e81"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"mylist", ",", "mylist"}], "}"}], ",", 
  RowBox[{"Joined", "->", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"True", ",", "False"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"218714b2-c784-614a-8b41-38487d6ed6dd"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"mylist2", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", 
       RowBox[{"F", "[", "x", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "3", ",", "0.02"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"847e3bad-4951-e041-9ee7-76b425c5aa03"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", "mylist2", "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"96c90b51-2bb0-2047-a076-8d84e9751e48"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"mylist2", ",", 
   RowBox[{"Joined", "->", "True"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"6e1214b3-7a2c-0b49-8fdd-2aa997274b46"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"mylist2", ",", 
   RowBox[{"Joined", "->", "True"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"InterpolationOrder", "->", "3"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785664487032795`*^9, 
  3.978566449233179*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a96d5b26-bdaa-3446-86fa-\
e9b504a426c8"],

Cell["\<\
(* For lines through points, ListLinePlot is a readable alternative; add \
PlotLegends to distinguish series. When combining multiple plots, you can \
also use Show to overlay graphics with consistent PlotRange. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"9dca9edf-c968-164b-bc5d-8df1da6723be"],

Cell["\<\
As another example, we create plots for G[x,c] vs. x for two different values \
of c; show both on one graphic:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cbb3d985-bd49-2b4d-8814-97959c85ea80"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"G", "[", 
   RowBox[{"x_", ",", "c_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
    RowBox[{"c", " ", "x"}], "]"}], "/", "x"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"a9baadfb-312d-4d41-bd1a-8e016cac4a72"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"myplot1", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"G", "[", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "1"}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "10", ",", "10"}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"PlotStyle", "->", 
     RowBox[{"RGBColor", "[", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "1"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"501afb0c-2a6f-6b4b-ab46-b15a434d5600"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"myplot2", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"G", "[", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "2"}], "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "10", ",", "10"}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"PlotStyle", "->", 
     RowBox[{"RGBColor", "[", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"98e79cd0-a195-964d-9172-d6f55a15fa3a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Show", "[", 
  RowBox[{"myplot1", ",", "myplot2"}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"9d8673ec-4cf6-7b47-b0df-3d6369c1373e"],

Cell["This could also be obtained with:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ce3d41f5-fff0-9647-a28e-4541c30b0ba1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"G", "[", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", "1"}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"G", "[", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", "2"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "10"}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotStyle", "->", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"RGBColor", "[", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", "0", ",", "1"}], "]"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"RGBColor", "[", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", "0", ",", "0"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotRange", "->", "All"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"b4259c59-1b9c-8746-9879-4445743eed95"],

Cell["\<\
Note: In Mathematica 6.0 and later, one can also use names for colors, e.g., \
Blue, Red.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fd54f302-55aa-8246-ab06-9ff03c1a6d0f"],

Cell["\<\
Other names include Green, Yellow, Orange, Purple, Black, and Gray.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b0947b65-d5fa-1946-a6ce-7b27c3b56cd8"],

Cell["\<\
(* At x==0, Sin[c x]/x is removable; for a continuous plot, use G[x_, c_] := \
Piecewise[{{c, x == 0}}, Sin[c x]/x] or set Exclusions -> None. Prefer named \
colors and Plot Theme for consistency across devices. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"bba7cde2-ea79-0b48-91f0-ab7a92495d6f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Series expansions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"988eb18e-a8cd-0f4e-9b57-6d3ef8743d1b"],

Cell["\<\
A useful command is Series, which creates a power series expansion.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b799b0ec-4a29-fb4f-a3aa-0c20a64001a9"],

Cell["\<\
Series [f, {x, x0, n}] gives a power series for f about x=x0 up to terms of \
order (x - x0)^n.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a02c3565-29f2-4e4e-a57c-2a982747eae4"],

Cell["For example, around x = 0 for Sin[x]:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ae62f13c-4b9f-314f-9ad1-29ded8c29086"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Series", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "x", "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "5"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID\
->"60fddb6f-2b8b-e54d-8bf8-631b8cd05308"],

Cell["\<\
(* Convert a SeriesData object to an ordinary expression with Normal [...] \
before further algebra/plotting: Normal@Series [Sin [x], {x, 0, 5}]. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"51b37ccc-ebcd-a04a-a4c9-bc706d727000"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Taylor", "[", "x_", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"Normal", "@", 
   RowBox[{"Series", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "x", "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "5"}], "}"}]}], 
    "]"}]}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978565178238493*^9, 3.978565201282919*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[44]:=",ExpressionUUID->"a700fbba-04ed-ee4c-a3f2-0d1b390a6406"],

Cell["PadeApproximant[f, {x, x0, {n,m}] gives a Pade approximant.", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785630629686584`*^9, 
  3.9785630931933823`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1d15608a-fbde-f247-9f01-\
a229f5bb8cb6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Pade", "[", "x_", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"PadeApproximant", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "x", "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"3", ",", "3"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978562734442007*^9, 3.9785627829697914`*^9}, {
  3.9785652065222816`*^9, 3.978565210385721*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[45]:=",ExpressionUUID->"13edba97-d199-2945-95d3-3fecd7ae92d5"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FractionBox[
  RowBox[{"x", "-", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"7", " ", 
     SuperscriptBox["x", "3"]}], "60"]}], 
  RowBox[{"1", "+", 
   FractionBox[
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "20"]}]]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978562746381529*^9, 3.9785627835443745`*^9}, 
   3.978565211432413*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[45]=",ExpressionUUID->"53c0a401-01f4-8c44-9c22-d14ff603eecc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "InterpolatingPolynomial[{{",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "0dfddc46-c5fb-1d48-9830-72e3f748ae8a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "ca858009-7292-4249-96b0-377b58ef49ad"],
 "}, {",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "3c79ded2-c942-df41-8030-86251618024a"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "edc15d69-a852-1241-9f9d-439441aa4ee9"],
 "}, ...}, x] constructs a Lagrange interpolating polynomial for the function \
values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "i"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "ad905b6f-7d38-1345-846b-f4f6a7307036"],
 " corresponding to x values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "i"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "dedc8ce8-8ca9-604d-9a94-0daed5e41b6b"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978564019265278*^9, 
  3.978564173760769*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6d466b73-9121-8f41-8452-\
21af288d8693"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"p", "[", "x_", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"InterpolatingPolynomial", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "0", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "2"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
         RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "2"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"Pi", ",", 
        RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "Pi", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}], ",", "x"}], 
   "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978562845882227*^9, 3.9785629756691227`*^9}, {
  3.978565119381706*^9, 3.978565122875307*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[40]:=",ExpressionUUID->"c295148e-aecd-774d-8c8b-dec2fd1586ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "InterpolatingPolynomial[{{",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "7f92e1c5-9865-3443-9d2e-d43645b363df"],
 ", {",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "5771c285-03d5-0c4a-86da-f00a67c839a9"],
 ",",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["df", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "729a8cd5-59ae-4846-8cb6-345ca9618118"],
 "}}, {",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "d92e2ce5-34f7-504f-a004-133a023958f7"],
 ", {",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "69cc0281-7917-2947-9fb4-4ae8bc77ba90"],
 ",",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["df", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "9d015060-fe58-b048-994b-ae91781225f5"],
 "}}, ...}, x] constructs a Lagrange interpolating polynomial for the \
function values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "i"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "66374a00-f946-664e-a142-44eca75d96fe"],
 " corresponding to x values ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "i"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "71377229-6929-0440-b30d-266cba0e4db1"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978564019265278*^9, 3.978564173760769*^9}, {
  3.978565032009001*^9, 3.978565071438139*^9}, {3.978565126248745*^9, 
  3.978565131203266*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"10dcf8d7-6d6f-374b-8d91-\
603465cb1291"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"h", "[", "x_", "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{"InterpolatingPolynomial", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "0", "]"}], ",", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Sin", "'"}], "[", "0", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "2"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
           RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "2"}], "]"}], ",", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Sin", "'"}], "[", 
           RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "2"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"Pi", ",", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "Pi", "]"}], ",", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Sin", "'"}], "[", "Pi", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}], 
    ",", "x"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978565076640751*^9, 3.978565137373514*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[41]:=",ExpressionUUID->"068f0f81-3aa4-1a41-b317-20cba9d3407f"],

Cell["Compare the series and the exact expression graphically:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.978566574573395*^9},ExpressionUUID->"5e821c96-9237-3e45-afbb-\
3ff6602ed179"],

Cell["\<\
Plot[{Sin[x],Taylor[x],Pade[x],p[x],h[x]}, {x, 0, 4}, 
 PlotStyle -> {Black,Blue, Red, Green, Orange}]\
\>", "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785627965336647`*^9, 3.9785628054034214`*^9}, {
  3.97856298370883*^9, 3.9785630216758366`*^9}, {3.978565221482544*^9, 
  3.9785652606469917`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[48]:=",ExpressionUUID->"a6f9b184-668a-9e41-9d99-bb5a345e0007"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Solving Equations", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7560b2f6-7cd0-9a40-b91d-8c66dace93d3"],

Cell["\<\
Another useful command is Solve. Solve [eqns, vars] solves equations for \
variables vars.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"af92e16b-c157-554f-9611-7354edf0f924"],

Cell["\<\
(Numeric version: NSolve.) Example: simultaneous equations x == a + by and y \
== c + dx.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e8a861cd-0994-5b4b-9050-8a410673a979"],

Cell["\<\
Because some symbols have been used previously, we begin by clearing x, y, a, \
b, c, d using Clear.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"45aa0c9f-cdb8-2541-bc2d-f57d1737a488"],

Cell["\<\
Note the use of == for equations (whereas = assigns a value).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"653c8ebc-5315-1f4c-9c27-cb440f96f098"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Clear", "[", 
  RowBox[{"x", ",", "y", ",", "a", ",", "b", ",", "c", ",", "d"}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[55]:=",ExpressionUUID->"78dcc0f8-92bf-8c4b-87ee-6bc94feab663"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"x", "==", 
      RowBox[{"a", "+", 
       RowBox[{"b", " ", "y"}]}]}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"y", "==", 
      RowBox[{"c", "+", 
       RowBox[{"d", " ", "x"}]}]}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"x", ",", "y"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[56]:=",ExpressionUUID->"53d7aa71-320f-c949-a254-cd40c5cc468d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"x", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"a", "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "c"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"y", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"c", "+", 
        RowBox[{"a", " ", "d"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]}]}], "}"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9785667409751205`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[56]=",ExpressionUUID->"dfb9d25b-5f6d-234f-9c4a-264c778e24d4"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"mysol", "=", 
  RowBox[{"Solve", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"x", "==", 
       RowBox[{"a", "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "y"}]}]}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"y", "==", 
       RowBox[{"c", "+", 
        RowBox[{"d", " ", "x"}]}]}]}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", "y"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[57]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d6e4136f-e634-d149-86d7-b9a46c49f58d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"x", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"a", "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "c"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"y", "\[Rule]", 
     RowBox[{"-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"c", "+", 
        RowBox[{"a", " ", "d"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]}]}], "}"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9785667432257767`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[57]=",ExpressionUUID->"2962a165-ad56-f74d-a8d8-80581437fdfd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"xsol", "=", 
  RowBox[{"mysol", "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", "1", ",", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978566749019827*^9, 3.9785667552524853`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[58]:=",ExpressionUUID->"09800bd9-14f1-f14c-9815-b2dbddf56e77"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"a", "+", 
    RowBox[{"b", " ", "c"}]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.978566758188755*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[58]=",ExpressionUUID->"d56ac552-ac19-6945-b5d0-7ada3ed7cea0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ysol", "=", 
  RowBox[{"mysol", "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", 
    RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785667604336376`*^9, 3.9785667649402447`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[59]:=",ExpressionUUID->"09cd31ad-b41f-5345-9356-cdbdc7a67a16"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"c", "+", 
    RowBox[{"a", " ", "d"}]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.978566765713066*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[59]=",ExpressionUUID->"1ae6f00a-632d-b947-911a-3069550b153d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"xsol", "-", "a", "-", 
  RowBox[{"b", " ", "ysol"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[60]:=",ExpressionUUID->"3e79fcfb-a15f-4b43-99ec-0190dad3f50a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"-", "a"}], "-", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"a", "+", 
    RowBox[{"b", " ", "c"}]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]], "+", 
  FractionBox[
   RowBox[{"b", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"c", "+", 
      RowBox[{"a", " ", "d"}]}], ")"}]}], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.97856677020298*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[60]=",ExpressionUUID->"da03c0c9-178e-364c-9689-b03eef6e9b12"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
  RowBox[{"xsol", "-", "a", "-", 
   RowBox[{"b", " ", "ysol"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[61]:=",ExpressionUUID->"ea2921cb-20b4-3c40-b101-10072a15a102"],

Cell[BoxData["0"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.978566776866274*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[61]=",ExpressionUUID->"b7fcac56-cd24-1144-9e37-7ebff68ce09a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
  RowBox[{"ysol", "-", "c", "-", 
   RowBox[{"d", " ", "xsol"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[62]:=",ExpressionUUID->"59862752-6fbe-0a46-8eaf-94aa2d4158ad"],

Cell[BoxData["0"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.978566778710579*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[62]=",ExpressionUUID->"9200384f-34de-c94f-911d-b076f7af14f0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
This technique can be used to test equality of expressions: compute \
Simplify[A - B] (or FullSimplify) and check for 0.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"21fc1078-da86-8942-88b2-bd55fe13b9d9"],

Cell["\<\
(* Solve returns rules; keep them as rules for substitution (expr /. sol \
[[1]]). For parameter domains, wrap in Assuming [...] or supply Reals to \
Solve/Reduce for clarity. *)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"38673b24-8c12-af4a-80e8-bc30c480b8c2"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"x", " ", "==", " ", 
     RowBox[{"a", " ", "+", " ", 
      RowBox[{"b", " ", "y"}]}]}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"y", " ", "==", " ", 
     RowBox[{"c", " ", "+", " ", 
      RowBox[{"d", " ", "x"}]}]}]}], "}"}], "//.", "mysol"}]], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978566819461628*^9, 3.9785668979056664`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[65]:=",ExpressionUUID->"b3189b7c-4ea6-b64d-a723-869aeacb73bb"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"a", "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "c"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}], "\[Equal]", 
     RowBox[{"a", "-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"b", " ", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"c", "+", 
          RowBox[{"a", " ", "d"}]}], ")"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{"c", "+", 
        RowBox[{"a", " ", "d"}]}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}], "\[Equal]", 
     RowBox[{"c", "-", 
      FractionBox[
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"a", "+", 
          RowBox[{"b", " ", "c"}]}], ")"}], " ", "d"}], 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"b", " ", "d"}]}]]}]}]}], "}"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785668549704533`*^9, 3.9785668983902664`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"Out[65]=",ExpressionUUID->"adc5b8d9-04a1-354a-bfa9-1223539debd5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"x", " ", "==", " ", 
      RowBox[{"a", " ", "+", " ", 
       RowBox[{"b", " ", "y"}]}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"y", " ", "==", " ", 
      RowBox[{"c", " ", "+", " ", 
       RowBox[{"d", " ", "x"}]}]}]}], "}"}], "//.", "mysol"}], "//", 
  "Simplify"}]], "Code",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978566819461628*^9, 3.9785669119567184`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[66]:=",ExpressionUUID->"7dfe3b05-6605-4444-a2da-ac43a622768d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"True", ",", "True"}], "}"}], "}"}]], "Output",
