Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Final comments on defining and evaluating expressions in Mathematica\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"630fe176-d9e0-0e44-8568-3da5c44b7ce7"],

Cell["\<\
You need to be careful in defining expressions and in using the correct \
values of variables in these expressions.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"71457ee9-e2dd-4740-8412-459f7c21aced"],

Cell["\<\
Errors may occur if the value of a variable is changed during the course of a \
session and you subsequently evaluate an expression containing that variable \
without realizing the value changed.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"82f401a7-8f79-dd4f-96c4-44476f66faf7"],

Cell["\<\
Be especially mindful if you scroll back to an earlier command and re-enter \
it after values have changed.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1c4f145d-db7a-5a45-a609-55706a004bab"],

Cell["\<\
When an expression is defined by a command such as f = Sin[10x]E^(-x), the \
left-hand side is immediately assigned the right-hand side.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7f669a87-68c2-e74c-9597-217cd4322412"],

Cell["\<\
It is essential that x has not been given a specific value before the \
definition;\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d28b145b-8bad-984a-b160-09a8e916355e"],

Cell["\<\
otherwise f immediately becomes a number (e.g., x = 1 would make f = \
Sin[10]E^(-1)), and subsequent calculations or plots of f will return that \
fixed value.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3df82074-ca97-8647-a026-9f381e799bef"],

Cell["\<\
As a precaution, it is good practice to Clear[x] before defining f.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"21fd6db2-62b4-2b45-9008-87872a347932"],

Cell["\<\
Assuming f has been properly defined, setting x=1 and then evaluating f gives \
Sin [10] E^(-1);\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"281a2420-9b34-bc45-bd03-ec261a0978e3"],

Cell["\<\
changing x=2 gives Sin [20] E^(-2); clearing x returns f to Sin[10x]E^(-x).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b7a9a172-9ea1-4240-aa41-999253d08b30"],

Cell["\<\
Whenever in doubt about the current meaning or value of a symbol, enter it by \
itself and see the output.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d8cdb097-aec5-b747-abdc-6709c67bf63e"],

Cell["\<\
If the output echoes the symbol, it is not currently defined.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7046ebf1-ee00-f041-b74a-cafcf3d9055e"],

Cell["\<\
A useful command that clears definitions in the current context is \
Clear[\"Global`*\"].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ad7bf26d-6d00-7247-bb94-0fea7bd10f8c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For more on defining expressions and functions, and for many useful \
commands and examples see ",
 ButtonBox["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/"]
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"33f26fbd-5471-9b4e-ba15-2b45892a3f59"],

Cell["\<\
(* To remove attributes/definitions more thoroughly, use ClearAll [symbol] or \
Remove [symbol]. For a clean slate without relaunching, use Evaluation Quit \
Kernel. For classroom notebooks, keep small cells, add comments in Text \
cells, and verify exact vs numeric results with Simplify and N side-by-side. \
*)\
\>", "Text",
 FontSlant->"Italic",
 Background->GrayLevel[
  0.95],ExpressionUUID->"1033edea-e65c-344c-bf31-7a1ca3e529b7"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
